WEBVTT

00:06.464 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

01:00.685 --> 01:05.940
MARCH 2021

01:06.900 --> 01:08.151
Hello, sir.

01:09.736 --> 01:11.571
You don't have to bow like that
with our team.

01:12.280 --> 01:14.199
Ah… [chuckles softly] Okay.

01:15.283 --> 01:17.744
Dawn is a good time for programming.

01:18.787 --> 01:19.746
It's quiet.

01:33.635 --> 01:35.345
As for Grandma and Grandpa,

01:36.638 --> 01:38.097
they're so happy I got a job

01:38.723 --> 01:41.351
that they're always picking up tabs
for people in town.

01:42.018 --> 01:43.311
[gentle music playing]

01:43.394 --> 01:44.521
And Hui-seo…

01:45.438 --> 01:46.356
[chuckles]

01:47.148 --> 01:48.233
He's even more thrilled.

01:49.150 --> 01:50.568
He's always saying he's happy.

01:51.820 --> 01:53.279
I've never seen someone

01:53.947 --> 01:55.907
who says that out loud.

01:57.867 --> 01:59.452
I thought it was just a word.

02:03.164 --> 02:05.333
[sighs] It's peculiar.

02:08.002 --> 02:09.045
As for me…

02:12.382 --> 02:13.883
Well… [inhales]

02:16.136 --> 02:17.971
Does it even matter?

02:24.144 --> 02:31.109
STILL SHINING

02:32.026 --> 02:34.028
-[music fades]
-[engine whirring]

02:34.112 --> 02:36.614
[woman over PA]
<i>The train is now approaching.</i>

02:37.490 --> 02:41.953
SEPTEMBER 2025

02:43.580 --> 02:46.082
[pleasant music playing]

02:51.880 --> 02:52.922
In position.

02:59.220 --> 03:01.347
Doors opened. Screen doors opened.

03:18.323 --> 03:19.866
[woman over PA] <i>The doors are closing.</i>

03:20.783 --> 03:22.201
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

03:22.285 --> 03:24.495
<i>-The screen doors are closing.</i>
<i>-</i>[train doors beeping]

03:29.959 --> 03:31.169
TRAIN OPERATOR 231
YEON TAE-SEO

03:37.759 --> 03:39.761
-[music fades]
-Hello.

03:39.844 --> 03:41.054
-Tae-seo, we're here.
-Hey.

03:41.137 --> 03:42.639
-I'm off.
-Hey, Tae-seo. You're going?

03:42.722 --> 03:44.140
-[Tae-seo] Last train?
-Yeah.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.142
At least we saw each other. See you later.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.436
-Good luck.
-[all] Bye. Good luck.

03:49.395 --> 03:50.855
-Ma'am, I…
-We ordered for you.

03:50.939 --> 03:52.148
[in English] Oh, thank you.

03:52.732 --> 03:55.568
-[in Korean] Do you want a drink?
-I'm on the 6:01 a.m. train tomorrow.

03:55.652 --> 03:56.778
I have to leave right after.

03:57.946 --> 04:00.073
[man] I know we eat fast for work,
but slow down, man.

04:00.156 --> 04:01.115
[Tae-seo chuckles]

04:01.199 --> 04:03.243
[soft music playing]

05:07.181 --> 05:08.641
[Hyeong-seok groaning]

05:11.227 --> 05:12.562
[Tae-seo] When did you get here?

05:13.104 --> 05:16.107
I was going to see Mi-ju after doing
errands for Dad, but she's busy.

05:16.691 --> 05:17.942
Geez. I'm hungry.

05:18.026 --> 05:19.527
Let's make some <i>ramyeon.</i>

05:19.610 --> 05:22.822
[panting] I forgot to hook up the gas.
You know I don't cook at home.

05:23.406 --> 05:25.199
You've forgotten for three years. Geez.

05:25.283 --> 05:27.493
[Tae-seo grunts] My goodness.

05:27.577 --> 05:28.661
[Hyeong-seok groans]

05:28.745 --> 05:31.247
-Sure. It happens.
-[lock beeping]

05:31.331 --> 05:32.707
It's whatever you want, after all.

05:38.087 --> 05:41.090
[exclaims] This is too much.

05:41.174 --> 05:43.718
Sure. I guess it's okay to live like this.

05:45.053 --> 05:46.679
What is this?

05:51.934 --> 05:54.145
-[clicks]
-[machine whirring]

05:58.649 --> 05:59.484
[lever clicks]

05:59.567 --> 06:01.569
-[loud whirring]
-[Hyeong-seok exclaims]

06:02.862 --> 06:04.155
[loudly] It can be a bit loud.

06:06.866 --> 06:08.451
-[clicks]
-[machine whirring stops]

06:09.827 --> 06:12.080
It's too loud to do this at night.

06:12.955 --> 06:15.249
Hey, why do you live like this?

06:16.000 --> 06:16.834
[shushes]

06:18.336 --> 06:19.754
[Hyeong-seok sighs in frustration]

06:21.881 --> 06:22.882
[groans]

06:26.260 --> 06:27.720
-[frustrated sigh]
-[thuds]

06:27.804 --> 06:29.013
See you later.

06:29.680 --> 06:30.515
[sighs]

06:31.474 --> 06:32.934
Quit looking at me like that.

06:33.017 --> 06:35.061
-Don't point at me. Do this.
-Go.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.109
[sighs softly]

06:42.360 --> 06:45.822
[Hui-seo over phone]<i> Why are you telling</i>
<i>me to attend Mr. Mu's sister's wedding?</i>

06:45.905 --> 06:47.365
<i>You should go.</i>

06:47.448 --> 06:49.033
You know I don't have weekends off.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.493
Come on.

06:51.160 --> 06:53.371
You always say you're busy
and never drop by.

06:54.997 --> 06:56.874
Let me know if anything's broken.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.334
<i>I'll come right away to fix it.</i>

06:58.417 --> 07:02.171
Does something have to break
for you to come home?

07:02.255 --> 07:04.674
<i>Don't you feel sorry for me? Huh?</i>

07:04.757 --> 07:07.176
<i>Honestly, I don't ever</i>
<i>bother you or anything</i>

07:07.260 --> 07:10.179
<i>while I take care of Grandma and Grandpa.</i>

07:10.263 --> 07:12.723
<i>Why are you always busy</i>
<i>whenever I call you?</i>

07:12.807 --> 07:14.183
Here it goes again.

07:14.267 --> 07:16.352
[Hui-seo] <i>If you were busy dating,</i>
<i>then it'd be fine.</i>

07:16.436 --> 07:18.146
<i>But you need to see someone</i>
<i>to get married.</i>

07:18.229 --> 07:19.939
<i>Then, I can have nieces and nephews.</i>

07:20.022 --> 07:21.607
<i>That way, I can be an awesome uncle.</i>

07:21.691 --> 07:23.734
-[Tae-seo chuckles]
-[Hui-seo] <i>How about three kids?</i>

07:23.818 --> 07:25.111
-I'm hanging up.
-[Hui-seo] <i>What?</i>

07:25.194 --> 07:26.279
<i>-Hello--</i>
-[line disconnects]

07:28.072 --> 07:29.240
[chuckles softly]

07:29.323 --> 07:31.492
PLAYLIST

07:31.576 --> 07:33.578
[song plays over phone]

07:44.881 --> 07:45.882
[can hissing]

07:54.223 --> 07:55.391
[exhales]

07:57.435 --> 07:59.187
-[sighs]
-[song stops playing]

08:13.034 --> 08:14.243
[breathes heavily]

08:14.327 --> 08:18.664
YOUR ACCOUNT IS CURRENTLY STREAMING
ON A DIFFERENT DEVICE

08:22.210 --> 08:24.462
[melancholic music builds]

08:43.606 --> 08:45.608
[melancholic music playing]

09:21.561 --> 09:23.646
YOUR ACCOUNT IS STREAMING
ON A DIFFERENT DEVICE

09:26.315 --> 09:28.109
STOP OTHER DEVICE
AND STREAM ON THIS DEVICE?

09:28.192 --> 09:29.026
CANCEL

09:29.735 --> 09:31.737
[woman over PA]
<i>The train is now approaching.</i>

09:40.621 --> 09:41.789
[Tae-seo] <i>It's Eun-a.</i>

09:43.082 --> 09:46.002
DONGJAK STATION

10:10.693 --> 10:12.695
[music ends]

10:25.625 --> 10:27.460
-[staff] Ms. Mo Eun-a?
-Yes.

10:27.543 --> 10:29.086
[staff] Please come up this way.

10:31.464 --> 10:34.759
Most of our guests are solo travelers.

10:34.842 --> 10:38.262
Many of them are writers
who stay here for long periods.

10:38.804 --> 10:42.308
You need to ask the long-term guests
for housekeeping hours.

10:42.391 --> 10:44.810
And we outsource the cleaning
to another company.

10:45.770 --> 10:48.939
[chuckles] This is our new manager.

10:56.364 --> 10:59.075
-Here's the inventory list.
-Okay.

10:59.158 --> 11:01.869
[staff] Make sure to clock out
at 4:10 p.m. sharp.

11:01.952 --> 11:04.330
Our boss said you were a veteran

11:04.413 --> 11:07.291
and emphasized that I had
to remind you of when to clock out.

11:08.209 --> 11:11.212
We inform guests on the booking page
that this is an unmanned hotel,

11:11.295 --> 11:13.339
but there are always a few
who complain in reviews.

11:13.422 --> 11:16.175
So please remind them when they check in.

11:16.258 --> 11:18.469
Mmm… Also,

11:18.552 --> 11:21.514
you need to wear
white tops and black bottoms.

11:21.597 --> 11:24.433
You just need to get the colors right.
Did you bring your clothes?

11:24.517 --> 11:26.769
Yes. What about the manuals?

11:26.852 --> 11:28.479
I put all of them up on the monitor.

11:29.522 --> 11:31.982
-And the break room?
-This way.

11:44.120 --> 11:45.955
This is the break room.

11:49.333 --> 11:51.710
-I'll put this here for now.
-Okay.

11:51.794 --> 11:53.671
I wanted to look around the area.

11:55.798 --> 11:57.925
I heard you ran a guesthouse before.

11:58.008 --> 11:58.968
Where was it?

12:00.136 --> 12:01.345
What happened?

12:07.268 --> 12:09.937
At least you got to run your own business.
[chuckles softly]

12:10.020 --> 12:12.940
-Have you found a place to live?
-I had to leave in a hurry, so…

12:13.482 --> 12:15.192
My place is really nice.

12:15.276 --> 12:18.362
My roommate is great too.
And I'm moving out in two weeks.

12:19.405 --> 12:20.906
It's close by. I highly recommend it.

12:20.990 --> 12:23.742
[chuckles softly]
I'm telling you because you seem nice.

12:24.535 --> 12:25.744
Could I get your number?

12:26.370 --> 12:28.372
[gentle music playing]

13:15.669 --> 13:18.672
ELECTRONICS STORE

13:40.486 --> 13:41.862
[Eun-a]<i> It's been a while.</i>

13:52.831 --> 13:53.999
Hey.

13:55.459 --> 13:57.920
-[Ji-seon exclaiming excitedly]
-[Eun-a laughs]

13:58.546 --> 14:00.381
Eun-a.

14:00.464 --> 14:02.007
[Eun-a] How have you been?

14:04.635 --> 14:05.636
Let's go.

14:05.719 --> 14:07.596
Go.

14:07.680 --> 14:08.847
I'm so happy.

14:08.931 --> 14:09.890
[both chuckling]

14:11.517 --> 14:12.476
[Ji-seon] What is it?

14:21.694 --> 14:22.736
My dad's photo.

14:28.242 --> 14:29.618
I came by to pick it up.

14:30.703 --> 14:32.830
Oh, you can take these bed sheets.

14:32.913 --> 14:33.747
They're new.

14:33.831 --> 14:35.374
Luxury hotels use them.

14:35.457 --> 14:36.750
You should use them.

14:37.668 --> 14:39.420
You'll need them if you're settling here.

14:40.004 --> 14:41.088
They look expensive.

14:41.171 --> 14:43.549
I shipped these to give them to you.

14:43.632 --> 14:46.010
I couldn't organize my things
since I left in a hurry.

14:46.093 --> 14:47.386
These were all I could grab.

14:52.099 --> 14:53.642
Are you hungry?

14:53.726 --> 14:54.602
Yeah.

14:57.563 --> 14:59.315
I didn't even get to visit Tongyeong.

15:00.399 --> 15:02.234
How can things happen like that?

15:02.318 --> 15:03.527
It's all over with.

15:03.611 --> 15:05.029
I'm actually relieved.

15:06.405 --> 15:08.032
When I closed down the guesthouse,

15:08.115 --> 15:10.492
I was upset, dumbfounded,
and heartbroken for months.

15:11.076 --> 15:12.578
But I'm relieved to let it go.

15:13.412 --> 15:14.747
[cutlery clinks]

15:20.252 --> 15:22.421
-Is this your mom's kimchi?
-[Ji-seon] Yeah.

15:22.504 --> 15:23.714
It's delicious.

15:23.797 --> 15:24.965
Eat up.

15:25.591 --> 15:27.384
-You can have all of it.
-[laughs]

15:29.053 --> 15:31.972
You can stay here
and take your time in finding a place.

15:33.265 --> 15:35.768
Although it's a bit far,
you can commute from here.

15:35.851 --> 15:37.394
No, I don't need to stay here.

15:37.478 --> 15:39.688
-I can sleep at my workplace.
-Since when?

15:39.772 --> 15:41.273
[Eun-a] I'm pretty lucky.

15:41.357 --> 15:43.400
I found a job in Seoul
within a couple hours.

15:43.484 --> 15:45.444
My predecessor
connected me with her old place.

15:45.527 --> 15:49.031
And my acquaintance will suddenly be away
for a week, so she said to stay there.

15:49.114 --> 15:49.949
It's in Seoul.

15:51.033 --> 15:54.119
Everything's been going smoothly
after I decided to come to Seoul.

15:54.995 --> 15:56.205
Still,

15:56.288 --> 15:59.625
if where you're staying isn't good,
you can come back here.

15:59.708 --> 16:00.960
Seung-jun said you could too.

16:01.710 --> 16:04.380
[door lock beeping]

16:04.463 --> 16:05.297
[groans]

16:05.881 --> 16:07.758
-He's drunk again.
-[beeping continues]

16:07.841 --> 16:09.843
-I told him to come home early today.
-[door opens]

16:09.927 --> 16:11.887
[Seung-jun] Why do you keep
changing the passcode?

16:11.971 --> 16:14.014
[slurring loudly] Eun-a!
You don't have to come out!

16:14.098 --> 16:16.016
Stay there, Eun-a! It's okay!

16:16.100 --> 16:17.309
You're so loud!

16:18.102 --> 16:19.269
[Seung-jun exclaims]

16:19.353 --> 16:21.897
-I told you to come home early.
-[chuckling] Eun-a.

16:22.606 --> 16:23.565
Well…

16:23.649 --> 16:25.901
Look how we've all made it!

16:25.985 --> 16:30.948
Middle schoolers from the country
have reunited in Seoul.

16:31.031 --> 16:32.241
This is Suwon.

16:33.283 --> 16:34.118
Have you been well?

16:34.201 --> 16:35.452
As if.

16:35.536 --> 16:39.289
Eun-a, you're the one
I envy the most in the world.

16:39.373 --> 16:40.416
Zip it and go away.

16:40.499 --> 16:42.126
-Do you know why?
-[Ji-seon] Hurry.

16:42.209 --> 16:43.961
-Go wash your hands.
-You quit a job.

16:44.044 --> 16:45.295
-You stink.
-You get a new one.

16:45.379 --> 16:46.964
-[exclaims]
-You quit and get a new one.

16:47.047 --> 16:49.633
You go to all the great spots
like Namhae and Tongyeong.

16:49.717 --> 16:51.635
-Not to mention Hawaii, right?
-Go inside!

16:51.719 --> 16:55.514
I want to live freely too now!

16:55.597 --> 16:57.599
-[door closes]
-[Ji-seon] Geez, will you zip it?

16:58.434 --> 17:00.227
It's been a while since we've seen her…

17:03.022 --> 17:07.067
[woman over PA] <i>This stop is Dongjak.</i>

17:07.151 --> 17:10.362
<i>The doors are on your right.</i>

17:10.446 --> 17:14.199
[in English] <i>This stop is Dongjak.</i>

17:16.744 --> 17:18.746
[slow instrumental music playing]

17:26.712 --> 17:32.009
[woman over PA in Korean]
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

17:44.772 --> 17:49.693
<i>The train for Buramsan is now approaching.</i>

17:51.278 --> 17:53.280
[cellphone vibrating]

17:58.535 --> 18:00.537
[train railings squeaking, hissing]

18:01.371 --> 18:02.790
May I have your attention, please?

18:02.873 --> 18:06.585
We will stand momentarily to maintain
proper distance between trains.

18:10.839 --> 18:12.174
[sighs wearily]

18:13.300 --> 18:14.551
[cellphone continues vibrating]

18:14.635 --> 18:16.053
SEONG-CHAN

18:16.136 --> 18:17.346
[cellphone stops vibrating]

18:32.986 --> 18:34.863
[woman over PA] <i>The doors are closing.</i>

18:35.656 --> 18:39.034
Doors closed. Screen doors closed.
Train departing.

18:55.050 --> 18:57.052
[music fades]

20:13.670 --> 20:14.838
[sighs softly]

20:18.217 --> 20:21.261
[Eun-a] I'll be staying in Seoul
for a bit starting today,

20:21.345 --> 20:23.513
just as you stayed
in Yeonwoo for a bit, Dad.

20:24.640 --> 20:25.724
I'll be in Seoul.

20:27.476 --> 20:28.769
Just for a moment too.

20:30.687 --> 20:31.688
[footsteps in distance]

20:31.772 --> 20:34.691
-[guest 1] What was our room number?
-[guest 2] It's the room at the end.

20:36.652 --> 20:38.654
[song playing over phone]

20:50.499 --> 20:53.669
[mouthing]

21:06.181 --> 21:07.391
[mumbles] It's 13 millimeters.

21:08.058 --> 21:08.892
Thirteen.

21:18.235 --> 21:19.528
[song stops playing]

21:33.292 --> 21:34.710
[sighs softly]

21:35.836 --> 21:36.962
Hello?

21:38.922 --> 21:41.133
Sure. Got it. I'll change it.

21:41.675 --> 21:42.592
[Tae-seo] <i>I forgot.</i>

21:43.677 --> 21:44.678
Okay, bye.

21:44.761 --> 21:46.722
[Tae-seo] <i>I had forgotten</i>
<i>that I shared my account</i>

21:46.805 --> 21:48.140
[line disconnects]

21:48.223 --> 21:50.100
<i>and the reason for sharing it.</i>

21:50.183 --> 21:51.310
[sighs]

21:52.311 --> 21:53.478
<i>I had forgotten all about it.</i>

22:09.286 --> 22:10.787
-Hello.
-Hello.

22:10.871 --> 22:12.497
-[woman] Stay Youngwon?
-Yes.

22:12.998 --> 22:14.374
[chuckles] Here you go.

22:14.458 --> 22:16.168
-Thank you.
-[woman] Sure. Have a nice day.

22:16.251 --> 22:17.210
You too.

22:22.049 --> 22:23.633
[Eun-a] Thank you for your work, ma'am.

22:23.717 --> 22:24.760
[chuckles, gasps]

22:24.843 --> 22:26.303
What's with the flowers?

22:27.220 --> 22:29.306
It's to celebrate my first day of work.

22:29.389 --> 22:30.974
Just for the first week.

22:31.058 --> 22:32.684
It's a personal ritual.

22:57.084 --> 23:00.962
[woman over PA]<i> This stop is Isu,</i>
<i>Chongshin University Station.</i>

23:01.046 --> 23:02.422
<i>The doors are on your right.</i>

23:02.506 --> 23:05.509
[train railings squeaking]

23:12.557 --> 23:14.601
[door hydraulics hissing]

23:15.227 --> 23:16.478
In position.

23:17.270 --> 23:20.440
<i>-</i>[over PA 1] <i>The screen doors are opening.</i>
<i>-</i>[over PA 2] <i>The doors are opening.</i>

23:20.524 --> 23:22.567
Doors opened. Screen doors opened.

23:22.651 --> 23:25.487
[woman over PA] <i>Please watch your step.</i>

23:25.570 --> 23:30.033
[man over radio] <i>Train 4654,</i>
<i>please stop for an additional minute.</i>

23:31.118 --> 23:33.620
This is Train 4654.
Request for stop is loud and clear.

23:35.080 --> 23:36.081
[Tae-seo clears throat]

23:36.623 --> 23:38.917
[Tae-seo over speaker]
<i>May I have your attention, please?</i>

23:40.627 --> 23:42.754
<i>To maintain proper distance</i>
<i>with the train ahead,</i>

23:42.838 --> 23:46.925
<i>we will be standing</i>
<i>for one minute before departing.</i>

23:49.427 --> 23:50.595
[Eun-a]<i> Tae-seo.</i>

23:55.100 --> 23:57.102
[emotional music playing]

24:28.175 --> 24:32.304
[man over radio]
<i>Train 4654, you may depart now.</i>

24:33.722 --> 24:37.142
[woman over PA] <i>The doors are closing.</i>

24:57.621 --> 24:59.706
Doors closed. Screen doors closed.

25:00.498 --> 25:01.625
Train departing.

25:02.250 --> 25:04.419
[train doors beeping]

25:23.188 --> 25:28.735
[woman over PA] <i>Please watch your step.</i>

25:46.920 --> 25:49.256
LAST TRAIN FOR OIDO
LAST TRAIN FOR ANSAN

25:54.803 --> 25:57.722
-[music fades]
-[cellphone vibrating]

25:57.806 --> 25:59.766
UNIT 610

26:03.061 --> 26:05.605
I'm on my way. I'm at Isu Station.

26:05.689 --> 26:09.276
[Ho-sik] <i>Hey, that Seong-chan guy</i>
<i>called me out of the blue.</i>

26:09.359 --> 26:12.028
<i>After I told him</i>
<i>you were coming to my place today,</i>

26:12.112 --> 26:14.197
I realized we'd be in trouble
if he barges in here.

26:16.116 --> 26:19.494
Na-yeong thinks we know each other
through Seong-chan.

26:19.577 --> 26:22.831
<i>I told him you'd call me</i>
<i>when you got to Isu Station</i>

26:22.914 --> 26:25.417
<i>and we'd meet there.</i>
[chuckles wryly] <i>I just rambled on and on.</i>

26:26.293 --> 26:28.169
<i>He won't be waiting</i>
<i>for you there, will he?</i>

26:31.172 --> 26:32.799
[Eun-a] I'll call you back.

26:39.973 --> 26:41.558
What are you doing here?

26:43.351 --> 26:44.436
Eun-a.

26:48.106 --> 26:49.274
[exhales]

26:51.484 --> 26:52.652
Let's go to Tongyeong.

26:52.736 --> 26:53.778
No.

26:54.779 --> 26:55.905
I told you I needed a break.

26:55.989 --> 26:59.367
You disappeared after saying you'd go
and close down the guesthouse.

26:59.451 --> 27:02.579
[train railings squeaking]

27:02.662 --> 27:05.415
-[woman over PA] <i>The doors are opening.</i>
<i>-</i>[door hydraulics hissing]

27:26.519 --> 27:28.396
[Seong-chan yells] You have to know too!

27:44.037 --> 27:46.039
[melancholic music playing]

27:54.005 --> 27:55.256
[Seong-chan] Eun-a!

28:16.611 --> 28:17.612
Eun-a.

28:18.279 --> 28:19.656
Eun-a.

28:38.091 --> 28:40.093
[panting]

28:41.761 --> 28:43.054
Yeon Tae-seo.

28:57.861 --> 28:59.863
[music fades]

29:09.998 --> 29:11.166
[cellphone vibrating]

29:12.000 --> 29:13.501
SEONG-CHAN

29:14.210 --> 29:15.920
[cellphone continues vibrating]

29:31.269 --> 29:32.520
[cellphone stops vibrating]

29:35.940 --> 29:38.193
We've been colleagues for ten years.

29:38.276 --> 29:40.236
Why be on a break
when we weren't even a thing?

29:41.112 --> 29:44.157
That way, you couldn't contact me
and deliver the bad news.

29:44.240 --> 29:46.868
We worked as partners,
so we should share the closure.

29:47.452 --> 29:49.287
[inhales] Yes, we're colleagues.
Happy now?

29:50.371 --> 29:51.873
It's their typical move.

29:51.956 --> 29:54.667
If business is good, they kick out
those running it and take over.

29:54.751 --> 29:56.878
We were duped by malicious outsiders.

29:56.961 --> 29:58.963
It wasn't your fault.
When we win the suit--

29:59.047 --> 30:00.215
So what's in it for us?

30:00.298 --> 30:01.716
[yelling] We can't let them run…

30:04.886 --> 30:06.888
[gently] We can't let them
do business either.

30:06.971 --> 30:09.474
It'll also be a loss for them
if the suit drags on.

30:09.557 --> 30:10.934
I'll see this through to the end.

30:12.352 --> 30:14.354
[sighs] I really don't want to know.

30:15.188 --> 30:16.815
I don't want to hear about it.

30:16.898 --> 30:18.358
[bicycle bell rings]

30:25.824 --> 30:27.200
You've come so far.

30:28.368 --> 30:29.577
Why Seoul?

30:33.414 --> 30:35.166
I'll visit often.

30:35.250 --> 30:38.711
Don't. I hate going back and forth
and matching schedules.

30:41.005 --> 30:42.882
The job here is simple and easy.

30:43.633 --> 30:45.260
It's great for passing the time.

30:45.343 --> 30:46.511
I feel comfortable.

30:52.809 --> 30:54.727
You've been through so much.

30:55.979 --> 30:57.730
Get home safely.

31:08.616 --> 31:11.202
[emotional music playing]

31:16.374 --> 31:17.500
[sighs heavily]

31:41.941 --> 31:43.943
[bicycle bell rings]

32:09.677 --> 32:11.220
[exhales]

32:34.327 --> 32:36.329
[whirring]

32:52.136 --> 32:53.888
-[switch clicks]
-[whirring stops]

32:55.890 --> 32:58.810
-[switch clicks]
-[whirring stops]

32:58.893 --> 32:59.978
[blows]

33:00.061 --> 33:02.105
[cellphone vibrating]

33:02.188 --> 33:03.398
Hello, Mr. Mu.

33:03.481 --> 33:06.025
[Jeong-su] <i>Hey, why did you send</i>
<i>so much wedding gift money?</i>

33:06.651 --> 33:07.694
It's nothing.

33:07.777 --> 33:09.988
I should've been there.

33:10.071 --> 33:13.908
[Jeong-su] <i>You didn't have to come.</i>
<i>You're busy. And Hui-seo was very helpful.</i>

33:13.992 --> 33:17.620
<i>He collected all the money at reception</i>
<i>and handed out the meal tickets.</i>

33:17.704 --> 33:19.998
<i>More students came than expected,</i>
<i>so it was hectic.</i>

33:20.081 --> 33:21.874
<i>But Hui-seo took care of everything.</i>

33:21.958 --> 33:24.043
Did my classmates come too?

33:24.127 --> 33:26.087
[Jeong-su] <i>To call them</i>
<i>your classmates would be…</i>

33:26.170 --> 33:28.256
<i>The ones you might actually know…</i>

33:28.339 --> 33:29.716
Eun-a…

33:30.425 --> 33:32.468
You haven't heard from her, have you?

33:33.219 --> 33:36.305
[Jeong-su]
<i>No. No one's heard anything from her.</i>

33:36.389 --> 33:38.349
<i>You're not in touch</i>
<i>with her either, right?</i>

33:39.308 --> 33:40.685
No.

33:40.768 --> 33:42.103
[Jeong-su] <i>Was it last month?</i>

33:42.186 --> 33:44.480
<i>A petition was filed under Eun-a's name.</i>

33:45.189 --> 33:47.400
<i>I heard a document</i>
<i>was filed very clumsily,</i>

33:48.026 --> 33:50.653
<i>requesting to tear down her house.</i>

33:50.737 --> 33:51.738
[gentle music playing]

33:51.821 --> 33:53.906
<i>As you know,</i>
<i>my wife works at the town office.</i>

33:54.615 --> 33:58.578
<i>Demolishing a vacant house</i>
<i>requires a lot of complicated documents,</i>

33:58.661 --> 34:02.206
<i>but there was only one sheet of paper</i>
<i>with Eun-a's name on it.</i>

34:07.503 --> 34:08.796
It came in the mail.

34:10.256 --> 34:11.841
This document is nonsense.

34:11.924 --> 34:14.802
Demolishing a vacant house
creates truckloads of trash,

34:14.886 --> 34:16.763
so it requires a delivery address.

34:16.846 --> 34:18.056
They wrote down Eun-a's house.

34:18.765 --> 34:22.351
So after demolishing the house,
did they want the trash piled there?

34:23.478 --> 34:25.563
There's no phone number, so I'm at a loss.

34:28.357 --> 34:30.068
[Hui-seo] Huh? Hey, Tae-seo!

34:30.151 --> 34:31.652
What on earth?

34:31.736 --> 34:32.904
That's my brother. [chuckles]

34:32.987 --> 34:34.489
-[man] I see.
-[Hui-seo] Hey, Tae-seo!

34:34.572 --> 34:36.657
-He's the pride of Yeonwoo.
-[man] Right.

34:36.741 --> 34:38.076
[Hui-seo] What brings you here?

34:38.159 --> 34:39.243
You should've told me.

34:39.327 --> 34:41.245
-He's the one I always talked about.
-[exclaims]

34:41.329 --> 34:43.748
-My colleagues at the post office.
-Hello.

34:43.831 --> 34:44.749
This is my mentor.

34:44.832 --> 34:46.751
Hui-seo's told me a lot
about you. [chuckles]

34:47.877 --> 34:49.045
[scooter revving softly]

34:50.963 --> 34:52.215
[Hui-seo] Why are you here?

34:54.759 --> 34:56.886
Three years ago,
you suddenly showed up on a weekday

34:57.678 --> 35:00.515
and dropped a bomb,
saying you quit that big company.

35:01.265 --> 35:02.600
Damn it, I'm still traumatized.

35:02.683 --> 35:05.520
You complain whether I come or not.

35:05.603 --> 35:06.562
How's work?

35:06.646 --> 35:08.773
The post office can't run without me.

35:08.856 --> 35:10.691
Didn't I tell you that already?

35:11.359 --> 35:13.361
Don't you worry about me.

35:14.737 --> 35:15.988
That is true.

35:17.073 --> 35:20.118
You'd been so responsible your whole life.
Why are you acting up now?

35:20.201 --> 35:22.286
You only do whatever you want.

35:22.370 --> 35:26.457
I never imagined
I'd worry about you when I grew up.

35:32.213 --> 35:34.966
[Hwa-sun straining] Hey. Eat first. Okay?

35:35.049 --> 35:37.718
I couldn't prepare much
since you came without notice.

35:38.469 --> 35:41.347
[Tae-seo] I'll take care of this
since I'm here. Is there anything else?

35:41.430 --> 35:43.224
No. Just come and eat.

35:46.602 --> 35:47.937
Let's put this here.

35:48.020 --> 35:49.438
Grandpa is taking a while.

35:50.273 --> 35:53.359
He was a hard worker
when he worked on others' farms.

35:53.442 --> 35:56.445
Now that we have our own farm,
he basically lives there.

35:56.529 --> 35:58.531
It's good having our own farm, you know.

35:58.614 --> 36:02.451
[chuckling] We get to live in comfort
at this age thanks to our grandsons.

36:02.535 --> 36:03.661
[laughs]

36:03.744 --> 36:06.956
Goodness. I forgot the kimchi.
I'll go get it.

36:07.039 --> 36:10.001
-I'll go put this in the storage then.
-Okay.

36:25.224 --> 36:26.517
[brakes squeaking]

36:41.574 --> 36:46.537
MART

37:14.190 --> 37:16.359
Yes? What is it?

37:18.027 --> 37:19.737
Gosh, look who it is.

37:20.488 --> 37:21.489
How have you been?

37:21.572 --> 37:24.575
Uh, Eun-a was here, right?

37:25.159 --> 37:27.328
These vegetable drawings are hers.

37:28.079 --> 37:29.080
She doesn't come here.

37:30.122 --> 37:31.499
Excuse me.

37:44.095 --> 37:45.137
Please give this to her.

37:45.221 --> 37:46.639
010-0922-1109
YEON TAE-SEO

37:46.722 --> 37:48.975
I ran into her by chance in Seoul.

37:51.227 --> 37:52.395
Uh…

37:52.478 --> 37:55.106
Is Eun-a doing okay in Seoul?

37:56.357 --> 37:58.234
I don't think so.

37:59.819 --> 38:00.903
I only saw her by chance.

38:01.946 --> 38:04.824
You're wrong. She's fine.

38:10.121 --> 38:11.580
Here.

38:11.664 --> 38:14.834
She sends me Christmas cards every year.

38:14.917 --> 38:20.256
They were sent from hotels and hostels.
Those were places she worked.

38:21.173 --> 38:22.174
This one.

38:23.968 --> 38:25.261
It's from last year.

38:32.101 --> 38:33.602
[gentle music playing]

38:34.312 --> 38:36.314
[Eun-a]<i> Grandma, how have you been?</i>

38:37.064 --> 38:40.151
<i>I think I'll settle down here.</i>

38:41.610 --> 38:42.903
She's been well.

38:52.955 --> 38:54.040
[Tae-seo] <i>Stop.</i>

38:55.124 --> 38:56.167
<i>Let's stop…</i>

38:57.335 --> 38:58.836
<i>with the worries and everything else.</i>

39:00.171 --> 39:01.172
<i>No more.</i>

39:02.757 --> 39:04.759
[whirring]

39:21.067 --> 39:22.068
[whirring stops]

39:23.861 --> 39:26.364
[woman] <i>I'm attaching the photo</i>
<i>since it can be disclosed.</i>

39:26.447 --> 39:27.823
<i>It's 5 by 7 inches.</i>

39:27.907 --> 39:31.160
<i>No glass. With at least 10 cm of margin.</i>

39:32.078 --> 39:35.873
<i>You can find Citizens' Cultural Heritage:</i>
<i>Old House online.</i>

39:39.293 --> 39:41.003
I'LL FIND THE MEANING IF THE WORLD WON'T

39:41.087 --> 39:41.921
[Tae-seo]<i> In order,</i>

39:42.713 --> 39:46.175
they're oak, cherry, walnut, and maple.

39:47.051 --> 39:48.177
See how they would look.

39:51.472 --> 39:53.349
You can either leave margins

39:53.974 --> 39:56.227
or pull the frame in tighter.

39:57.853 --> 39:59.313
Hmm…

40:01.023 --> 40:02.024
This one.

40:03.442 --> 40:05.986
Leaving margins would be nice.

40:06.070 --> 40:07.530
Can we use traditional paper?

40:07.613 --> 40:08.989
[Tae-seo] Yes, we can.

40:11.075 --> 40:12.284
What's your day job?

40:16.622 --> 40:17.790
I'm a train operator.

40:18.916 --> 40:20.376
I see.

40:20.459 --> 40:21.836
And you're not working today?

40:21.919 --> 40:24.046
I work tomorrow afternoon.
It's a night shift.

40:24.839 --> 40:26.715
A total of five. And your name?

40:28.175 --> 40:30.302
Im A-sol.

40:30.386 --> 40:31.929
Ms. Im A-sol.

40:33.264 --> 40:34.807
The type of wood is oak.

40:35.641 --> 40:36.976
By the third week…

40:38.477 --> 40:40.104
of next month. Is that right?

40:41.021 --> 40:42.857
What's good about being a train operator?

40:44.275 --> 40:45.401
Well…

40:46.777 --> 40:50.030
It's good because I can't bring work home.

40:50.114 --> 40:52.533
[exclaims] That's awesome.

40:52.616 --> 40:53.951
[Tae-seo] I have a question too.

40:54.660 --> 40:56.912
What made you decide
to commission me for this job?

40:57.496 --> 41:00.040
I've never done this for anyone
other than my colleagues.

41:00.958 --> 41:02.501
It was at a restaurant.

41:03.252 --> 41:07.840
A landscape photo had a frame worthy
of being in an art gallery, so I asked.

41:07.923 --> 41:10.384
And I checked the social media account
written on the back.

41:11.260 --> 41:14.346
Also, can I commission you
for another frame?

41:14.430 --> 41:16.599
This one has no deadline.
It's for an oil painting.

41:16.682 --> 41:19.018
Uh, how big is it?

41:19.101 --> 41:20.978
Well, it's about…

41:21.061 --> 41:22.313
About this big?

41:22.396 --> 41:25.024
Or maybe this big?

41:26.567 --> 41:27.526
[Tae-seo] Um…

41:28.360 --> 41:30.404
[inhales sharply]
Please give me five minutes.

41:33.532 --> 41:34.575
Sorry?

41:46.420 --> 41:47.296
What on earth?

41:53.135 --> 41:55.095
[A-sol panting]

41:55.179 --> 41:57.598
-This is it.
-Do you live close by?

41:57.681 --> 41:59.767
-Yes.
-I'll…

41:59.850 --> 42:03.437
This is the first painting I ever bought.

42:03.521 --> 42:05.981
It dropped on the floor
when its string broke,

42:07.358 --> 42:09.318
and the frame was smashed.

42:09.401 --> 42:12.947
I've never worked with a painting before.
It really is huge.

42:13.030 --> 42:15.074
Good. I wanted a completely new frame.

42:16.408 --> 42:18.035
Roughly, how big is it?

42:19.370 --> 42:20.829
I don't have a measuring tape.

42:22.122 --> 42:23.832
No, it's okay.

42:23.916 --> 42:26.418
You can take actual measurements at home
and send them to me.

42:26.502 --> 42:27.670
Okay.

42:29.213 --> 42:30.965
[Tae-seo] Let me take a photo first.

42:31.632 --> 42:32.716
Is that okay?

42:35.636 --> 42:36.887
[camera shutter clicks]

42:38.931 --> 42:40.724
-[exhales]
-[thuds]

42:40.808 --> 42:43.978
[camera shutter clicking]

42:44.061 --> 42:47.189
The restaurant's owner told me
the frame maker used to be a programmer.

42:47.273 --> 42:49.108
You're him, right?

42:49.191 --> 42:50.776
Which restaurant was it?

42:50.859 --> 42:53.445
The one under the study center.

42:53.529 --> 42:55.364
I see. Hyeong-seok's study center.

42:56.156 --> 42:57.866
Then, I guess that is me.

42:57.950 --> 43:01.245
So that was what you used to do. I see.

43:01.328 --> 43:02.871
Why? Did something happen?

43:04.456 --> 43:06.875
-[inhales]
-Well, as for me,

43:06.959 --> 43:08.460
stuff happened at home,

43:08.544 --> 43:10.337
and the frame that was fine for ten years

43:10.421 --> 43:12.256
fell on the floor when its string snapped.

43:12.339 --> 43:13.465
Isn't it strange?

43:14.925 --> 43:18.220
[clicks tongue] I guess such a question
would be bewildering since we just met.

43:19.138 --> 43:21.015
Well, nothing happened.

43:21.098 --> 43:23.475
And I get asked that all the time,
so I don't mind.

43:23.559 --> 43:26.437
Ah, I see.
You get asked that all the time.

43:27.271 --> 43:28.355
It was…

43:29.440 --> 43:31.650
a strange day for me too.

43:32.693 --> 43:36.405
It was as if moments of the past
were coming together and…

43:36.488 --> 43:37.823
[soft music playing]

43:37.906 --> 43:39.950
I'm not really good with words.

43:41.535 --> 43:44.079
But there was a day like that.

43:55.341 --> 43:57.259
Are you sure you don't need any help?

43:58.010 --> 43:58.927
I'm sure.

44:00.220 --> 44:01.639
[grunts]

44:27.706 --> 44:28.749
[sighs]

44:28.832 --> 44:33.545
REOPENING AFTER RENOVATION
MAEUM STUDY CAFÉ

44:39.510 --> 44:41.637
Did you see that it's a study café now?

44:41.720 --> 44:43.138
Yes, I did.

44:43.639 --> 44:47.267
It looked very bright
after unblocking all the windows.

44:47.351 --> 44:50.270
Back then, making it dark
made it better to focus.

44:50.354 --> 44:51.522
But now, it's about openness.

44:51.605 --> 44:54.400
They concentrate better
with people going back and forth.

44:54.483 --> 44:56.318
Ma'am, it's me.

44:56.402 --> 44:58.612
-[woman] Hey.
-[Hyeong-seok] Two spicy stir-fried pork.

44:59.613 --> 45:00.739
[Tae-seo] It was that one.

45:01.615 --> 45:02.908
[Hyeong-seok] You did that one.

45:02.991 --> 45:05.786
So you were the one
who told the owner here about my old job.

45:05.869 --> 45:07.830
What are you talking about
all of a sudden?

45:10.165 --> 45:11.333
Do you want to drink?

45:11.417 --> 45:13.085
-Oh, this is rare.
-[cellphone vibrating]

45:13.168 --> 45:14.378
You're getting a call.

45:25.681 --> 45:26.807
No.

45:29.810 --> 45:33.230
-It was an unknown number.
-Why did you answer it then?

45:33.313 --> 45:36.191
-Ma'am, a rolled omelet too!
-[woman] Okay.

45:45.617 --> 45:46.660
[Hyeong-seok exhales]

45:50.747 --> 45:52.249
For ten years, I'd forgotten.

45:53.542 --> 45:54.793
They were gone.

45:55.377 --> 45:57.921
But can old worries come back?

45:58.005 --> 46:00.716
If it's ten years ago,
that's after you got into college.

46:01.592 --> 46:03.552
Then, it's likely not
about your family. [inhales]

46:03.635 --> 46:06.305
You don't talk about the stuff
that really worries you.

46:07.681 --> 46:11.059
You were really going through it
before you did your military duty.

46:11.143 --> 46:13.604
[groans] It had to be about a girl,

46:13.687 --> 46:17.357
but you just wouldn't talk about it
because you said it would remind you.

46:17.441 --> 46:19.693
You said you'd die
if you spoke about it out loud.

46:19.776 --> 46:23.280
So if you're talking about it,
it's not a problem.

46:23.363 --> 46:25.240
If it's a real problem,
you never mention it.

46:25.324 --> 46:26.909
You're afraid it would worry you.

46:29.620 --> 46:30.996
Right.

46:31.079 --> 46:33.624
[chuckling] Geez. That was it.

46:33.707 --> 46:36.877
[sighs] I've worked as the study center's
manager for ten years.

46:36.960 --> 46:41.507
I'm at the peak of encouraging
and counseling the kids who don't study.

46:41.590 --> 46:43.383
"You matter. It's up to you in the end."

46:43.467 --> 46:46.720
"That guy lives his life
on his own terms."

46:46.803 --> 46:48.931
"He can't hold his liquor,
but whenever he drinks,

46:49.014 --> 46:51.600
he only thinks about what to do
and his direction in life."

46:51.683 --> 46:54.061
"You should focus on that too."

46:54.144 --> 46:56.939
"And he got into
Hanguk National University."

46:57.022 --> 47:00.025
"He used to sit in Seat One."
I end with promoting the study center.

47:00.108 --> 47:01.527
[grunts]

47:01.610 --> 47:05.489
So, stop bringing back old worries.

47:05.572 --> 47:06.657
Okay?

47:06.740 --> 47:10.035
Did you already forget the kind of future
your mom wished for you?

47:11.119 --> 47:14.122
"Something safe and peaceful."

47:14.873 --> 47:17.834
[sighs] I'm making that my family motto
when I get married.

47:18.669 --> 47:20.546
[slurring] Then, memorize it properly.

47:22.673 --> 47:24.633
[Hyeong-seok] This sure is peaceful.

47:26.343 --> 47:27.511
[sighs]

47:32.391 --> 47:33.976
[Tae-seo] <i>"Something safe and peaceful</i>

47:35.894 --> 47:38.230
<i>where he can make a living</i>
<i>without struggle."</i>

47:42.818 --> 47:46.947
JANUARY 2022

47:47.030 --> 47:48.323
Tae-seo.

47:48.407 --> 47:49.783
[Tae-seo] Yes?

47:49.866 --> 47:51.368
You've been dispatched

47:52.327 --> 47:54.079
to the India branch.

47:54.162 --> 47:57.249
We've worked with their research team,
so there will be familiar faces.

47:58.083 --> 47:59.084
It's a good opportunity.

47:59.918 --> 48:01.378
Yes, sir. I understand.

48:05.007 --> 48:07.009
-[Hui-seo over phone] <i>It's not a big deal.</i>
-[sighs]

48:07.092 --> 48:09.886
[Hui-seo] <i>But Grandpa fell</i>
<i>on his behind while weeding.</i>

48:09.970 --> 48:12.431
<i>The village head said he fainted.</i>

48:12.514 --> 48:14.016
<i>But he's just taking aspirin.</i>

48:14.099 --> 48:16.310
He should… He should go to the hospital.

48:17.769 --> 48:20.689
Make him get a prescription for medicine.
I'll drop by this weekend.

48:20.772 --> 48:23.108
[Hui-seo] <i>Don't worry.</i>
<i>Just visit during Lunar New Year.</i>

48:23.191 --> 48:25.944
<i>Busy people only come</i>
<i>on Lunar New Year and Chuseok.</i>

48:26.028 --> 48:29.656
<i>Things are running well around here</i>
<i>thanks to me. But it won't last.</i>

48:29.740 --> 48:31.241
<i>Enjoy your freedom.</i>

48:33.827 --> 48:35.704
<i>I saw Auntie Suk-hui today.</i>

48:35.787 --> 48:38.498
<i>Mom used to work with her at the station.</i>

48:38.582 --> 48:42.252
<i>She told me that I resembled Mom</i>
<i>whenever she'd get off work and say,</i>

48:42.336 --> 48:43.545
<i>"I love looking at the ocean."</i>

48:43.629 --> 48:46.298
-[Tae-seo]<i> It was a strange day.</i>
-[Hui-seo] <i>I guess I resemble Mom.</i>

48:47.758 --> 48:50.218
[Tae-seo] <i>In the morning,</i>
<i>I received an opportunity.</i>

48:50.302 --> 48:53.805
<i>I heard Hui-seo talk about Mom</i>
<i>when he usually doesn't.</i>

48:54.681 --> 48:58.560
<i>And in the afternoon, I gave up</i>
<i>the opportunity I received in the morning.</i>

48:58.644 --> 49:00.812
[Hyeong-seok]
<i>You don't want me to look into that room?</i>

49:00.896 --> 49:02.981
<i>Even though it's uphill,</i>
<i>it's a good price.</i>

49:03.065 --> 49:05.984
-I want you to look into it.
-[woman over PA] <i>The next stop is Dongjak.</i>

49:06.068 --> 49:08.528
-I'll call you back. Bye.
-[woman over PA] <i>The door is on…</i>

49:15.410 --> 49:17.579
<i>-The doors are closing.</i>
-Hey, Hyeong-seok.

49:17.663 --> 49:20.749
-[woman over PA] <i>The doors are closing.</i>
-Could you look into that room for me?

49:21.875 --> 49:24.836
I just got off the subway.
I couldn't hear a thing before.

49:27.839 --> 49:31.218
Well, something came up in the morning.

49:32.219 --> 49:33.220
Yeah.

49:34.137 --> 49:35.389
Okay, bye.

49:39.351 --> 49:40.477
[huffs]

49:49.361 --> 49:51.446
-[gentle music playing]
-[Tae-seo]<i> At that moment,</i>

49:51.530 --> 49:55.534
<i>I had a strong feeling that I knew</i>

49:55.617 --> 49:57.536
<i>what was important to me.</i>

49:57.619 --> 49:59.204
[boy] Mom!

50:00.205 --> 50:02.165
Tae-seo! [chuckles]

50:03.917 --> 50:06.878
[Tae-seo]
<i>Compared to how much Mom cared for me</i>…

50:06.962 --> 50:08.046
Wait just a bit.

50:08.130 --> 50:10.716
[Tae-seo] <i>I didn't even care</i>
<i>a tiny fraction for myself.</i>

50:13.802 --> 50:14.886
<i>"Where?"</i>

50:16.054 --> 50:18.390
<i>In case something happens at home,</i>

50:18.473 --> 50:20.809
<i>a distance that can be traveled in a day.</i>

50:23.562 --> 50:25.647
<i>Later on one day,</i>

50:26.690 --> 50:28.191
<i>I'll be doing what I want to do.</i>

50:29.609 --> 50:30.777
<i>"With who?"</i>

50:32.487 --> 50:33.488
<i>Myself.</i>

50:35.574 --> 50:37.409
<i>The one momentarily free</i>
<i>thanks to Hui-seo.</i>

50:39.453 --> 50:40.620
<i>With myself.</i>

50:43.790 --> 50:44.791
<i>Will it be possible?</i>

51:18.283 --> 51:24.915
CHONGSHIN UNIV (ISU)

51:29.961 --> 51:30.921
[Eun-a]<i> March.</i>

51:31.713 --> 51:35.175
<i>Every time around the start</i>
<i>of the school year, I thought of you.</i>

51:38.678 --> 51:42.641
<i>On the day of your parents' memorial,</i>
<i>I thought you'd be sad.</i>

51:45.727 --> 51:47.062
<i>I would think,</i>

51:48.104 --> 51:49.564
<i>"Should I call you?"</i>

51:50.607 --> 51:52.234
<i>And then, April would come.</i>

51:53.527 --> 51:55.654
<i>When summer comes, I can't do it.</i>

51:56.530 --> 51:58.740
<i>When autumn comes, it gets even harder.</i>

52:00.492 --> 52:03.453
<i>In the winter, I completely give up.</i>

52:06.081 --> 52:08.041
<i>I've repeated this for several years.</i>

52:11.628 --> 52:13.255
<i>But I'll stop now.</i>

52:15.173 --> 52:16.925
<i>Because I saw you.</i>

52:18.969 --> 52:20.679
[cellphone vibrates]

52:20.762 --> 52:22.138
MESSAGE FROM CORNER STORE GRANNY

52:23.014 --> 52:24.850
[Gyeong-chun]
<i>Tae-seo is worried about you.</i>

52:27.561 --> 52:29.938
010-0922-1109
YEON TAE-SEO

52:42.450 --> 52:44.703
[huffing]

52:51.293 --> 52:52.335
[exhales]

52:53.169 --> 52:54.254
MISSED CALL

52:57.090 --> 52:59.050
[panting]

52:59.134 --> 53:00.927
CALLS

53:12.856 --> 53:14.482
[line ringing]

53:25.577 --> 53:26.620
Hello?

53:29.706 --> 53:32.542
Sorry to call at this hour,
but I had a missed call.

53:34.419 --> 53:35.503
[Eun-a]<i> It's me.</i>

53:39.549 --> 53:41.927
<i>Why are you worried about me?</i>

53:42.010 --> 53:44.512
<i>That's what</i>
<i>the corner store granny told me.</i>

53:49.351 --> 53:50.477
Are you outside?

53:54.940 --> 53:55.941
Yeah.

54:00.946 --> 54:04.658
Can I call you back in a little bit?

54:04.741 --> 54:06.284
[Eun-a] <i>Okay.</i>

54:15.585 --> 54:16.795
[lock beeps]

54:16.878 --> 54:18.880
[panting]

54:45.490 --> 54:46.783
[cellphone vibrates]

54:50.286 --> 54:51.121
Hey.

54:54.040 --> 54:55.291
Hi.

54:57.627 --> 55:00.088
You're a train operator, right?

55:01.006 --> 55:04.384
<i>The corner store granny told me</i>
<i>you were a train operator in Seoul.</i>

55:05.301 --> 55:07.512
Do you commute to Isu Station?

55:08.221 --> 55:11.307
-<i>I heard it's different for each operator.</i>
-It's Dongjak Station.

55:11.391 --> 55:12.225
[Eun-a] <i>Ah</i>…

55:12.934 --> 55:14.477
<i>I see.</i>

55:17.605 --> 55:19.816
Train Operator Yeon Tae-seo.

55:21.067 --> 55:22.610
It suits you.

55:25.030 --> 55:27.490
[gentle music playing]

55:27.574 --> 55:29.826
<i>I called to tell you</i>
<i>not to worry about me.</i>

55:29.909 --> 55:32.871
<i>My situation wasn't good,</i>

55:32.954 --> 55:34.998
<i>so that might've made you worry.</i>

55:37.876 --> 55:39.502
What kind of situation was it?

55:42.005 --> 55:43.965
He wants to apologize to me.

55:44.549 --> 55:46.342
We had some stuff going on.

55:46.426 --> 55:47.719
It's a long story.

55:47.802 --> 55:49.846
[Tae-seo]
<i>He's your colleague from the hotel, right?</i>

55:52.015 --> 55:53.850
Be clear with him.

55:55.852 --> 55:57.562
That way, he won't show up out of the blue

55:59.439 --> 56:00.982
to apologize.

56:04.277 --> 56:07.072
-<i>If it's nothing to worry about--</i>
-It's not.

56:07.155 --> 56:08.406
Don't worry.

56:14.162 --> 56:16.081
Okay. It's late.

56:16.164 --> 56:18.583
-I'll hang up now.
<i>-</i>[Eun-a] <i>Okay.</i>

56:19.751 --> 56:20.752
[line disconnects]

56:29.260 --> 56:31.513
[telephone ringing]

56:37.894 --> 56:38.728
[ringing stops]

56:39.395 --> 56:41.356
NO ANSWERING THE PHONE AFTER WORK HOURS

56:51.533 --> 56:52.992
[cellphone vibrating]

56:55.328 --> 56:56.454
Hello, sir.

56:56.538 --> 56:57.956
[man] <i>You can't stay there.</i>

56:58.039 --> 57:00.792
<i>Please stick to the contract.</i>
<i>It's supposed to be an unmanned hotel.</i>

57:00.875 --> 57:02.335
I'm sorry.

57:02.418 --> 57:03.878
I came in a hurry, so…

57:04.546 --> 57:06.256
I have a place to stay
starting from today.

57:06.339 --> 57:08.174
[man] <i>It seems</i>
<i>one of the customers saw you.</i>

57:08.675 --> 57:11.386
<i>They asked me</i>
<i>if it really is an unmanned hotel.</i>

57:12.095 --> 57:15.515
<i>Please follow the rules,</i>
<i>or you'll put me in a tough position.</i>

57:22.480 --> 57:23.690
Eun-a.

57:24.774 --> 57:27.360
-I'm not late, am I?
-Not at all.

57:27.444 --> 57:30.822
I heard you got to Isu Station that day
but had to go back because of work.

57:30.905 --> 57:33.199
It would've been great
if we had dinner together then.

57:33.283 --> 57:37.829
-[chuckles] Ho-sik, Eun-a's here!
-[Ho-sik] I'm coming.

57:37.912 --> 57:40.582
-Did you bring the camera and batteries?
-[Ho-sik] Yeah.

57:40.665 --> 57:42.375
-I got everything. We're good.
-Good.

57:45.086 --> 57:47.213
Traveling is our job,

57:47.297 --> 57:50.758
but our dog and plants
made it hard to go on long trips.

57:50.842 --> 57:53.136
We're lucky to just have
the plants looked after. [laughs]

57:53.219 --> 57:55.096
We can be away for a while
thanks to Eun-a.

57:55.180 --> 57:56.222
[chuckles] That's right.

57:56.306 --> 57:58.683
It's nothing.
I'm the one who's truly grateful.

57:59.559 --> 58:00.894
You saved me.

58:01.728 --> 58:03.480
Come on. Let's go.

58:03.563 --> 58:05.398
She was waiting to see you.

58:05.482 --> 58:07.525
Hurry and get going.

58:07.609 --> 58:09.027
Please enjoy your trip.

58:09.110 --> 58:11.446
What was that?
You sound like a hotel manager.

58:11.529 --> 58:13.364
[Ho-sik and Na-yeong laughing]

58:13.448 --> 58:16.075
Take care of our place for us.

58:16.159 --> 58:17.577
-Have a good trip.
-[Na-yeong] Bye.

58:17.660 --> 58:18.495
Let's go!

58:18.578 --> 58:21.164
[Ho-sik] Let's go! We're late!

58:53.238 --> 58:54.322
[exhales]

58:55.782 --> 58:56.783
[Eun-a]<i> Dongjak Station.</i>

59:39.826 --> 59:43.037
-[train railings squeaking]
-[door hydraulics hissing]

59:43.121 --> 59:45.707
-[train doors beeping]
-[over PA] <i>The screen doors are opening.</i>

01:00:05.393 --> 01:00:06.769
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

01:00:06.853 --> 01:00:09.105
-[door hydraulics hissing]
<i>-The doors are closing.</i>

01:00:09.188 --> 01:00:10.732
<i>The screen doors are closing.</i>

01:00:10.815 --> 01:00:12.692
<i>Please stand back.</i>

01:00:14.402 --> 01:00:17.238
[doors hissing]

01:00:29.751 --> 01:00:31.753
[emotional music playing]

01:01:56.462 --> 01:01:57.797
[sobbing]

01:02:22.238 --> 01:02:23.865
[music fades]

01:03:17.668 --> 01:03:20.546
[melancholic music playing]

01:03:37.438 --> 01:03:38.773
It's been a while.

01:03:55.122 --> 01:03:58.626
STILL SHINING

01:04:24.735 --> 01:04:26.237
[Eun-a] <i>You really haven't changed.</i>

01:04:26.320 --> 01:04:29.240
[Tae-seo] <i>It's the same.</i>
<i>My feelings are the same.</i>

01:04:31.659 --> 01:04:33.953
<i>You're someone I liked ten years ago,</i>

01:04:34.537 --> 01:04:35.913
but I still feel the same way.

01:04:35.997 --> 01:04:38.207
[Eun-a]<i> All the things</i>
<i>you see every day in Seoul,</i>

01:04:38.291 --> 01:04:39.625
<i>I want to see too.</i>

01:04:39.709 --> 01:04:41.377
[Tae-seo] <i>Stay right by my side.</i>

01:04:41.460 --> 01:04:42.879
[Eun-a]<i> Granny!</i>

01:04:43.796 --> 01:04:46.757
[So-hyeon] <i>You just take back what's yours</i>
<i>and go back to living your life.</i>

01:04:47.425 --> 01:04:48.551
[Tae-seo]<i> Is he…</i>

01:04:49.719 --> 01:04:51.012
<i>weighing on you a lot?</i>

01:04:57.393 --> 01:04:59.395
Subtitle translation by: Hye Won Yoon
